  "title": "Lead Automation Engineer – Rockwell & Siemens Systems",
  "description": "<p>Experience:13–19+ Years<br />\nLocation: Singapore</p><p>Industry: Oil &\nGas, Marine, Semiconductor, Industrial Automation</p><p>Key Responsibilities</p><p>· Lead the design and architecture of automation systems using Rockwell and Siemens PLC, HMI, SCADA, and drive solutions</p><p>· Own end-to-end automation execution: design, programming, FAT, SAT, commissioning, and handover</p><p>· Define and enforce automation standards, best\npractices, and reusable libraries</p><p>· Lead legacy system migrations (PLC-5 / SLC to ControlLogix) and integration of new systems</p><p>· Review and approve PLC, HMI, and network designs developed by project teams</p><p>· Provide installation, commissioning, and on-site troubleshooting support for in-house and third-party systems</p><p>· Conduct system validation: testing, debugging, FAT, SAT, commissioning, and documentation</p><p>· Serve as the primary technical interface with customers, OEMs, and vendors</p><p>· Mentor and guide senior and junior engineers;\nperform technical reviews and knowledge sharing</p><p>· Support proposal preparation, pre-sales activities, project planning, and risk management</p><p>· Ensure compliance with cybersecurity, safety, and industry standards</p><p>· Maintain effective customer communication to\nmeet project requirements and ensure satisfaction</p><p>· Control Panel Expertise: Experience in design, troubleshooting, and commissioning is a plus</p><p>Job Requirements</p><p>· Education: Degree or Diploma in Electrical,\nElectronics, Control, or Instrumentation Engineering</p><p>· Experience: 13–19+ years in industrial automation and control systems, preferably with Rockwell platforms</p><p>· Technical Skills:</p><ul><li>PLCs: PLC-5, SLC, MicroLogix, CompactLogix, ControlLogix</li><li>SCADA/HMI: RSView32, FactoryTalk ME & SE, WinCC, PCS7, Wonderware</li><li>Drives: PowerFlex 700/753/755, Kinetix Servo Drives</li><li>Networking & Protocols: Ethernet/IP, DeviceNet, ControlNet, DH+, DH-485, RIO, Modbus</li><li>FactoryTalk: AssetCentre, Historian, Batch, IAB</li><li>OT cybersecurity and industrial networking knowledge is a plus</li></ul><p>· Work Environment: Willingness to work at local and overseas shipyards, offshore sites, adapting to varied conditions over extended periods</p><p>· Soft Skills: Strong leadership, mentoring, problem-solving, collaboration, and customer communication. Ability to manage scope, variation orders, and customer negotiations</p>",
